{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 16:40:52.565048", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Submission completed.\n\n- Is anomaly: true\n- Faulty devices: [\"web_server_0\"]\n- Root cause: [\"sender_application_delay\"]\n\nRationale\n- All network layers (core, distribution, server-access) show healthy OSPF adjacencies and consistent routing; ICMP reachability is clean with low RTTs.\n- DNS/DHCP paths and HTTP via the load balancer are functioning normally with stable TTFB.\n- The only deviation is elevated TTFB and total time when accessing web0.local directly, isolated to web_server_0.\n- With no network loss/jitter and other HTTP paths performing well, the most likely root cause is application/server-side delay on web_server_0 rather than a network issue.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2180, "output_tokens": 153, "total_tokens": 2333, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2048}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
